Long summary:
Regulates algorithmic recommendation services and requires services to implement guidelines and provisions including:

Establish management systems and technical measures for algorithm examination, user registration, information dissemination, security monitoring, incident response, data protection, and fraud prevention;

Conduct regular assessments of algorithms, models, data and application outcomes; 

Strengthen information security management and identify unlawful/harmful information;

Implement tactics to avoid user harms and prohibit dissemination of misinformation; 

Ban false account registration, trading, manipulation and anti-competitive practices; 

Implement specific guidelines for services targeting minors, the elderly, workers and consumers; 

Implement transparent and efficient complaint handling processes; 

Establishes graded/categorized algorithm management system and filing procedures for relevant department authorities charged with oversight of algorithmic recommendation services;

Authorizes relevant departments to carry out security assessments and inspections and;  

Specifies legal liabilities and penalties for violations.
